replyContent:
If you are using the GLideN64 based profiles, they used to be limited to either 2x or 3x game resolution. I removed that so that it actually runs at the selected display resolution. I would suggest lowering the display resolution so that it matches what it was before.

I will have to investigate the full screen issue. I'm not seeing that here.

I did add shader support, one of the shaders available is FXAA which is a form of anti-aliasing.

It's definitely possible. GLideN64 already supports MSAA but I don't have it enabled. MSAA would have to be supported by each video plugin. Audio effects it's possible, but that would take a lot of time to do and I don't think I have time.
